    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_01006">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Synthetic glucocorticoid. DEXA-ARDS trial (PMID 32043986): 20 mg IV QD days 1–5 then 10 mg QD days 6–10; 60-day mortality 21% vs 36% (P=0.005); +4.8 ventilator-free days. Only pharmacological agent with proven mortality benefit in non-COVID ARDS. Converges with RECOVERY trial to establish dexamethasone as cornerstone pharmacotherapy.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D059495</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C5203912</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>32678530</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dexamethasone treatment for hospitalized COVID-19</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_01121">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Repositioning of mechanically ventilated patient face-down for ≥16h per session. PROSEVA (PMID 23688302): 28-day mortality 16.0% vs 32.8%, HR 0.39 (0.25–0.63), P&lt;0.001. Indicated for severe ARDS (PaO₂/FiO₂ &lt;150). Mechanisms: reduction of dorsal atelectasis, V/Q redistribution, decreased physiological dead space.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0035222</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Mechanical prone ventilation</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PPV</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Prone position ventilation</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Proning</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>11529210</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>14668608</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>19903918</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>24102072</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>24435203</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>33464919</obo:source_pmid>
        <obo:source_pmid>33823862</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Prone positioning shows stronger benefit in focal ARDS (CT morphology). PMID:30342773</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">prone positioning</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_01360">
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D006440</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0020676</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_mechanism"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>33009098</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Fluid overload (ARDS risk mechanism)</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_02874">
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_outcome"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Avoided intubation</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03121">
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_context"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Severe ards duration over 72h</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03200">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Biologically distinct ARDS subphenotype identified by latent class analysis (Calfee et al. AJRCCM 2014; PMID 25030514). Characterised by elevated plasma IL-6 (&gt;400 pg/mL), IL-8, sRAGE, angiopoietin-2, PAI-1; vasopressor-dependent shock; metabolic acidosis; higher 90-day mortality. Differential response to higher PEEP compared to hypoinflammatory subphenotype. Heterogeneity of treatment effect (HTE): conservative fluid management associated with improved outcomes (lower PEEP may worsen; moderate-high PEEP may benefit). Possible immunomodulation benefit (baricitinib, dexamethasone). Real-time classification feasible using parsimonious 3-variable model (IL-8, Protein C, bicarbonate) without requiring full biomarker panel (Sinha 2020 PMID:32461733; Gao 2021; Calfee 2014 PMID:25030514).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0035222</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ARDS subphenotype 2</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Calfee phenotype 2</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Hyperinflammatory phenotype</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Reactive ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Type H ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Conservative fluid management shows mortality benefit in hyperinflammatory subphenotype (HTE: Calfee 2018 ARDS Network reanalysis).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Greater steroid benefit expected in hyperinflammatory subphenotype (anti-inflammatory mechanism aligns with phenotype biology; DEXA-ARDS converges with RECOVERY evidence).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">High EVLWI associated with hyperinflammatory subphenotype — supports conservative fluid strategy in this phenotype.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Hyperinflammatory subphenotype may benefit from HIGHER PEEP strategy. Also shows differential response to simvastatin (beneficial) and corticosteroids (dexamethasone, DEXA-ARDS convergence).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">IL-6 markedly elevated in hyperinflammatory ARDS. &gt;400 pg/mL threshold.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">IL-8 elevated; included in parsimonious 3-variable classifier.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Low bicarbonate = metabolic acidosis. Part of parsimonious classifier.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Mortality ~2.5x higher than hypoinflammatory in matched cohorts. More vasopressor-dependent shock, metabolic acidosis, multi-organ failure. Shorter ventilator-free days.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Protein C LOW in hyperinflammatory — procoagulant state, endothelial activation. Part of parsimonious classifier.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03201">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Biologically distinct ARDS subphenotype (Calfee et al. AJRCCM 2014; PMID 25030514). Low plasma inflammatory biomarkers, absence of vasopressor shock, lower 90-day mortality. Majority phenotype (~70%). Responds to lower PEEP. Low PEEP strategy preferred: high PEEP may increase mortality in hypoinflammatory subphenotype (ALVEOLI reanalysis; Calfee 2014). Protein C levels are HIGHER than hyperinflammatory; bicarbonate is normal. IL-8 levels LOW — key distinguishing feature in parsimonious classifier.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ARDS subphenotype 1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Calfee phenotype 1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory phenotype</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Type L ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Uninflamed ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory subphenotype responds better to LOWER PEEP. High PEEP may increase mortality in this subphenotype (secondary analysis, ALVEOLI trial; Calfee 2014 PMID:25030514).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Low PAI-1 is characteristic of hypoinflammatory subphenotype. In contrast to hyperinflammatory where PAI-1 is markedly elevated.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Protein C HIGHER in hypoinflammatory — partially protective anticoagulant/endothelial phenotype.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Hypoinflammatory ARDS subphenotype</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03202">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">CT-defined ARDS phenotype with unilateral or lobar consolidation. Recruitable at low pressures; high risk of overdistension with high PEEP. Gattinoni-Marini CT phenotype classification (PMID 30342773). Focal morphology (dorsal-caudal consolidations on CT/EIT/LUS): better response to prone positioning (gravitational redistribution). High PEEP and aggressive recruitment RELATIVELY contraindicated — higher risk of overdistension of aerated regions. Lower recruitability per electrical impedance tomography.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Focal lung involvement ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Lobar ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>30342773</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">EIT quantifies regional ventilation distribution — identifies focal consolidation pattern and recruitability in real time.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Focal ARDS: aggressive recruitment maneuvers relatively contraindicated (ART trial harm signal; focal morphology increases overdistension risk).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Focal ARDS: high PEEP relatively contraindicated — overdistension risk in aerated lung regions exceeds atelectasis benefit.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Focal ARDS: lower PEEP preferred (high overdistension risk). High PEEP strategy harmful in this morphology (ART trial mechanistic analysis). Responds to prone positioning.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Focal ARDS: stronger prone positioning benefit due to gravitational redistribution of dorsal consolidations. PMID:30342773</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Focal ARDS</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03203">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">CT-defined ARDS with diffuse bilateral ground-glass opacities. Low recruitability; may benefit from higher PEEP. Gattinoni-Marini (PMID 30342773). Non-focal / diffuse morphology: higher potential recruitability; may benefit from moderate-high PEEP to prevent atelectrauma. Recruitment maneuvers less harmful than in focal ARDS. Prone positioning less beneficial (diffuse involvement; less gravitational gradient). Mechanical power monitoring especially important — risk of overdistension at high PEEP if lung compliance does not improve.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Diffuse ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Non-recruitable ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>30342773</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">EIT identifies non-focal pattern: diffuse bilateral ventilation distribution. Guides PEEP titration in non-focal ARDS.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Non-focal ARDS: may benefit from higher PEEP to prevent atelectrauma. Lower recruitability. Prone less beneficial per CT morphology analyses.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Non-focal ARDS</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03205">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Pro-inflammatory cytokine. Plasma IL-6 &gt;400 pg/mL classifies hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype. Target of tocilizumab/sarilumab.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>CHEBI:138181</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D015850</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0085295</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">BSF-2</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">IFNB2</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">IL-6</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Interleukin 6</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Interleukin-6</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03206">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Neutrophil chemoattractant (CXCL8). Elevated in ARDS BAL and plasma; drives neutrophilic alveolitis. Elevated in hyperinflammatory subphenotype.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D016209</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0079633</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">CXCL8</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">IL-8</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">NAP-1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Interleukin-8</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03209">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Procoagulant inhibitor (SERPINE1). Elevated in hyperinflammatory ARDS; reflects antifibrinolytic state and alveolar fibrin deposition.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D017374</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PAI-1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">SERPINE1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>25030514</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Plasminogen activator inhibitor-1</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03213">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Selective JAK1/JAK2 inhibitor. RECOVERY 2022 (PMID 37320743): significant mortality benefit in hospitalised COVID-19 ARDS.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>CHEBI:90551</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:C000596027</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">LY3009104</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Olumiant</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>37320743</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Baricitinib</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03216">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Vt 2–4 ml/kg PBW + RR 10–14/min + Pplat ≤25 cmH₂O during VV-ECMO. Proposed mechanism of EOLIA benefit (PMID 29791822).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D015199</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ECMO lung rest</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Lung rest strategy</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>29791822</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Ultra-protective ventilation during VV-ECMO</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03217">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">VV-ECMO initiated as salvage after failure of all conventional strategies. EOLIA crossover: 57% of 35 crossover patients died.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D015199</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Refractory ARDS ECMO</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Salvage ECMO</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>29791822</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Rescue VV-ECMO</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03226">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Energy delivered to respiratory system per minute (J/min). &gt;17 J/min associated with increased ARDS mortality (PMID 28985207).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">MP</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Mechanical power ventilation</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_outcome"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>28985207</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Mechanical power</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03230">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">ARDS patients with echocardiographic acute cor pulmonale or RV dysfunction. Relative contraindication to high-PEEP and aggressive recruitment. Incidence 20–30% in moderate-severe ARDS by echocardiography. Mechanism: hypoxic pulmonary vasoconstriction + hypercapnia + PEEP → elevated pulmonary vascular resistance → RV pressure overload → RV dilation. High PEEP and aggressive recruitment can worsen RV afterload — relative contraindications. Prone positioning may paradoxically improve RV function by reducing hypoxic vasoconstriction. Echocardiographic monitoring recommended before escalating PEEP. PMID:20558628 + recent 2024 echo-ARDS studies.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D006333</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ARDS with acute cor pulmonale</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_population"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>20558628</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Aggressive recruitment maneuvers increase RV afterload via transient high airway pressures — avoid in confirmed RV dysfunction.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">High PEEP increases RV afterload → may precipitate acute cor pulmonale.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Right ventricular dysfunction ARDS population</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03270">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Life-threatening syndrome of acute diffuse inflammatory lung injury. 2012 Berlin criteria: acute onset within 1 week of clinical insult; bilateral opacities on imaging; PaO₂/FiO₂ ≤300 mmHg on PEEP ≥5 cmH₂O; not fully explained by cardiac failure or fluid overload. Severity: mild 200&lt;P/F≤300; moderate 100&lt;P/F≤200; severe P/F≤100 mmHg. PMID 22360949 (JAMA 2012 Berlin Definition).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D012128</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:22360949</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0035222</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>biolink:Disease</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ALI</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Acute lung injury</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Berlin definition ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Non-cardiogenic pulmonary oedema</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_disease"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Acute respiratory distress syndrome</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03271">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Soluble receptor for TNF-α (sTNFR1/TNFRSF1A). Elevated in hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype; associated with 90-day mortality. 2024-2025 literature refines its role alongside PAI-1 as a high-performance biomarker panel.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D019834</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">TNFR1 soluble</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">TNFRSF1A soluble form</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">sTNFR1</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Soluble tumour necrosis factor receptor 1</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03280">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Ventilator-delivered mechanical power (MP) to the respiratory system exceeding 17 J/min — the dose-dependent mortality threshold established in ARDS cohorts (Serpa Neto 2018 PMID:28985207; Coppola 2024). MP = 0.098 × RR × Vt × [Peak pressure − PEEP/2]. Higher MP associated with VILI regardless of subphenotype, but hyperinflammatory and non-focal phenotypes may be more susceptible. Threshold varies by analysis (17–18.7 J/min across studies).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:28985207</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Elevated MP threshold</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">High mechanical power ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">MP &gt;17 J/min</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_outcome"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>28985207</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">EIT enables regional distribution of mechanical power — identifies overdistension hot-spots not visible from global MP calculation.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Elevated driving pressure is the dominant contributor to mechanical power. ΔP reduction is the primary lever for MP control.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Mechanical power exceeding 17 J/min</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03281">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Real-time bedside classification model using only 3 readily available variables — IL-8 (plasma), Protein C (plasma), and Bicarbonate (serum) — to distinguish hyperinflammatory from hypoinflammatory ARDS subphenotype. AUROC ~0.90 in validation cohorts. Avoids need for full cytokine panel. Enables rapid treatment personalisation in ICU settings. Sinha 2020 (PMID:32461733); Maslove 2022.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:32461733</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">3-variable ARDS subphenotype model</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Bedside ARDS phenotyping tool</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">IL-8 Protein-C Bicarbonate classifier</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>32461733</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Bicarbonate: acid-base variable reflecting metabolic acidosis.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">IL-8: primary inflammatory variable in parsimonious model.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Parsimonious classifier targets this subphenotype for classification.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Protein C: coagulation/endothelial variable.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Parsimonious ARDS subphenotype classifier</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03282">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Anticoagulant serine protease. LOW plasma Protein C is a key feature of hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype; HIGHER levels characterise hypoinflammatory phenotype. Part of the parsimonious 3-variable classifier (Sinha 2020 PMID:32461733). Reflects endothelial activation and procoagulant state in ARDS.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D017148</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:32461733</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>UMLS:C0072020</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Coagulation factor XIV</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PC</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PROC</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>32461733</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Protein C</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03283">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Serum bicarbonate (HCO3-). LOW bicarbonate reflects metabolic acidosis — a key feature of hyperinflammatory ARDS subphenotype. Used as the third variable in the parsimonious 3-variable classifier (alongside IL-8 and Protein C). Normal or elevated bicarbonate characteristic of hypoinflammatory phenotype (PMID:32461733).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>LOINC:1963-8</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D001639</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Bicarbonate serum level</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">HCO3-</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Plasma bicarbonate</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Serum HCO3</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_biomarker"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>32461733</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Serum bicarbonate</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03284">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Restrictive fluid strategy targeting zero or negative cumulative fluid balance in ARDS. FACTT trial (PMID:16714767): negative fluid balance improved oxygenation and reduced ventilator days without increasing renal failure. HTE analysis (Calfee 2018): mortality benefit concentrated in hyperinflammatory subphenotype. Liberal fluid may worsen pulmonary oedema, especially in hyperinflammatory patients.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:16714767</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">FACTT conservative arm</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Fluid conservative ARDS management</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Negative fluid balance ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Restrictive fluid strategy ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_intervention"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>16714767</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Conservative fluid management strategy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03285">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Ventilation strategy using PEEP &gt;10–12 cmH₂O, typically guided by ARDSNet high-PEEP/FiO₂ table or transpulmonary pressure titration. Benefits vary strongly by ARDS subphenotype and CT morphology: beneficial in non-focal (diffuse) ARDS; potentially harmful in focal ARDS (overdistension) and in RV dysfunction (elevated afterload). Must be distinguished from individualized PEEP (PROBESE, iPROVE).</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:28973363</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Elevated PEEP ventilation</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">High PEEP ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">High PEEP strategy</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_context"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>28973363</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">High PEEP ventilation strategy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03286">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">High sustained inflation pressure (&gt;40 cmH₂O) recruitment maneuvers aimed at opening collapsed lung. ART trial (PMID:28973363): HR 1.20 for 28-day mortality — definitive harm in unselected moderate-severe ARDS. Relatively contraindicated in focal ARDS (overdistension), RV dysfunction (afterload), and hypoinflammatory subphenotype. May have a role in non-focal ARDS with high recruitability.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>PMID:28973363</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">ART-style recruitment</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Aggressive RM</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">High-pressure recruitment ARDS</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_context"/>
        <obo:source_pmid>28973363</obo:source_pmid>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Aggressive recruitment maneuver strategy</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
    <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://poi-kb.org/ards/ARDS_POI_03287">
        <obo:IAO_0000115 xml:lang="en">Extravascular lung water index (EVLWI) and Pulmonary Vascular Permeability Index (PVPI) measured via transpulmonary thermodilution. EVLWI &gt;10 mL/kg and PVPI &gt;3 indicate increased permeability pulmonary oedema (ARDS pattern). Used for phenotype-guided fluid management: high EVLWI in hyperinflammatory subphenotype favours conservative fluids. Low EVLWI with high PVPI suggests early permeability oedema.</obo:IAO_0000115>
        <obo:hasDbXref>MESH:D062080</obo:hasDbXref>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">EVLWI</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">Extravascular lung water</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PVPI</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:hasExactSynonym xml:lang="en">PiCCO EVLW</obo:hasExactSynonym>
        <obo:inSubset rdf:resource="http://poi-kb.org/ards/POI_outcome"/>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Extravascular lung water index</rdfs:label>
    </rdf:Description>
